{"title":"Thomson Bike Tours goes Beyond Tarmac w/ new gravel bike trips","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/28/thomson-bike-tours-goes-beyond-tarmac-w-new-gravel-bike-trips/","date":1624912596000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>The new Thomson gravel bike tours promise all the hospitality, gorgeous scenery, and top-notch destinations and food as their road bike tours, just not on a paved road. With four European routes to choose from, and more coming, you now have some pretty rad ways to see a new country on the roads less traveled.</p><p>Here are the details for each of the currently scheduled trips, followed by a few teasers for others coming online this year…</p><h3>Provence &amp; Mt. Ventoux Gravel</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb20/ng:webp/ngcb20\" alt=\"thomson bike tours gravel road trip up mont ventoux in france\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb20/ng:webp/ngcb20\" ezoid=\"0.6757411303177849\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28160223/how-to-ride-up-mt-ventoux-on-on-gravel-roads-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 630w\"></a></p><p>Always wanted to climb the legendary Mont Ventoux in France? Or already done it and want a fresh challenge? Thomson’s found an off-road route to the top, with rustic roads through lavender fields and old cities before aiming upward and finishing at the famous antennas on the roof of the mountain.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8lNIjU7cwB0?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>This 7 day/6 night gravel tour is one of the tougher ones, with a minimum recommended tire width of 700×40. Next scheduled ride departs on September 12, 2021.</p><p>Price is for each of these trips is $3,295 per person, and all trips include gear transport between stops, accommodations, and all meals.</p><h3>Tuscany Gravel</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region.jpg\" alt=\"guided gravel bike tours on strade biancha in tuscany italy\" width=\"1422\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region.jpg 1422w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-747x420.jpg 747w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1422px) 100vw, 1422px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region.jpg 1422w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28161253/thomson-bike-tours-guided-gravel-bike-trip-through-tuscany-wine-region-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a></p><p>Ride the pristine Strade Biancha’s crushed white stone as you pass cypress trees en route to chianti, olive oil, and likely lots of fresh pasta and other amazing Italian food.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ipbxRj3sL7I?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>This one’s a little easier, and smoother, but no less gorgeous (maybe more so…it is Italy after all). Next trip starts October 3rd, 2021.</p><h3>Girona &amp; Catalonia Gravel</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours.jpg\" alt=\"riding gravel bikes on forest roads in girona spain with thomson bike tours\" width=\"1422\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours.jpg 1422w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-747x420.jpg 747w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1422px) 100vw, 1422px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours.jpg 1422w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28162414/gravel-bike-riding-in-girona-catalan-spain-on-thomson-bike-tours-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a></p><p>Ride from Girona into the Pyrenees, then back to the Mediterranean Sea on this 7 day/6 night tour. You’ll ride through a national park, past extinct volcanoes, and in birch tree forests while exploring the Catalan countryside.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9xELhUNzjFo?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>This one’s medium difficulty with a few singletrack sections and a bit of technical terrain, but not as much climbing as Ventoux. Next trip starts October 24th, 2021.</p><h3>Portugal-Algarve Gravel</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast.jpg\" alt=\"riding gravel bikes on rocky cliffs in portugal along the coast with thomson bike tours new off road trips\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28163314/riding-gravel-bikes-on-singletrack-in-portugal-on-the-coast-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Start near the border of Spain and work your way toward, then down the coast on a mix of cobble roads, singletrack, and gravel paths over 7 days. This area is one of Thomson’s staff favorites, it winds through pine trees and eucalyptus forests before edging high above the water for spectacular views.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wrPKVoUPCf8?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>This one’s medium difficulty, too, thanks to a more mixed set of surfaces you’ll be riding, but includes two nights at a resort with thermal baths. Next trip is November 14, 2021.</p><p>Look for additional trips in Morocco to come soon, plus one in Vermont in the fall to catch all those changing leaves.&nbsp;Get all the details, more photos, and a daily itinerary with mileage on their website.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.thomsonbiketours.com/trip-calendar/trips/gravel/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>ThomsonBikeTours.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"c86abb217fa6463c53b9168ef4350b4872bd81fb578b139bc3796f1781dbdacb","category":"Cycling"}